; =============================================================================
; ci.mon — VICE moncommands for headless CI test run
; =============================================================================
; VICE loads this file on startup. The sequence is:
;   1. loadsym    — load test_suite symbols so "td_spin" resolves
;   2. break      — set breakpoint at td_spin (completion spin-loop)
;   3. go         — start the CPU; test suite runs to completion
;   4. (VICE hits td_spin breakpoint, re-reads next commands)
;   5. save       — write 1-byte PRG from $07E8 (off-screen scratch RAM)
;   6. quit       — exit VICE
;
; pass_count is written to $07E8 immediately before td_spin (in both
; pass and fail paths), so the value is stable when the breakpoint fires.
; $07E8 is off-screen scratch RAM (past the 40x25 = $07E7 last byte).
; =============================================================================

loadsym tests/test_suite.vs
break td_spin
go
save "tests/ci_result.bin" 0 07e8 07e8
quit
